        <prompt>How did Theodore Roosevelt earn his Nobel Peace Prize?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Ending the Civil War</option>
            <option letter="b">Mediating the Russo-Japanese War</option>
            <option letter="c">Creating national parks</option>
            <option letter="d">Building the Panama Canal</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Theodore Roosevelt won the 1906 Nobel Peace Prize for successfully mediating the Treaty of Portsmouth, which ended the Russo-Japanese War of 1904-1905.</explanation>
