    <question>
        <prompt>What was the main achievement of the Pure Food and Drug Act of 1906?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It banned all imported food</option>
            <option letter="b">It required honest labeling and inspection</option>
            <option letter="c">It made all drugs illegal</option>
            <option letter="d">It regulated farm prices</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Pure Food and Drug Act required truthful labeling of food and drugs, prohibited harmful additives, and established federal inspection of meat products, protecting consumer safety.</explanation>
