        <options>
            <option letter="a">It eliminated all private banks</option>
            <option letter="b">It created a central banking system</option>
            <option letter="c">It banned paper money</option>
            <option letter="d">It increased interest rates</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Federal Reserve Act of 1913 established America's central banking system, creating a more stable and flexible banking system through regional Federal Reserve banks.</explanation>
